Description: Mark demo executable buffer with PROT_EXEC to fix NX segfault
 The demo code is loaded into heap memory allocated via calloc().  On
 Linux with NX (No-Execute) support, heap pages are mapped rw-p by default,
 causing a SIGSEGV when the CPU attempts to fetch instructions from the
 demo's entry point.
 .
 After allocating the demo buffer (exeofs), call mprotect() to set
 PROT_READ|PROT_WRITE|PROT_EXEC on the covering pages.  The address is
 rounded down to the nearest page boundary and the size is rounded up
 accordingly, so the call is safe for both large (mmap-backed, always
 page-aligned) and small (sbrk-backed) allocations.
